  <exercise>
    <statement>
    <p>Let <m>G</m> be a group and let <m>H\leq G</m> have index 2. Prove that <m>H\unlhd G</m>.</p>
    </statement>
    <solution>

    <p>
     Let <m>a\in G</m>. If <m>a\in H</m>, then <m>aH=H=Ha</m>. On the other hand, if <m>a\not\in H</m>, then <m>aH=G-H=Ha</m>, since <m>(G:H)=2</m>. Thus, <m>H\unlhd G</m>.

    </p>
  </solution>
  </exercise>

<exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>Let <m>G</m> be an abelian group with <m>N\unlhd G</m>. Prove that <m>G/N</m> is abelian.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
 
    <p>Let <m>aN,bN\in G/N.</m> Then <me>(aN)(bN)=abN=baN=(bN)(aN).</me> So <m>G/N</m> is abelian.
     
    </p>
  </solution>
  </exercise>


<exercise>
<statement>
<p>
Find the indices of:
<ol>
<li><m>H=\langle(23)\rangle</m> in  <m>S_3</m>;</li>
<li><m>K=\langle(1254)(23)\rangle</m> in <m>S_5</m>;</li>
<li><m>L=\langle(1245)(25)\rangle</m> in <m>S_6</m>.</li>
</ol></p>

</statement>

<solution>
<p>
<ol><li><m>(S_3:H)=|S_3|/|H|=6/2=3</m>.</li>
<li>In disjoint cycle notation, the permutation <m>(1254)(23)</m> is written <m>(12354)</m>, so <m>K</m> has order 5. Thus, <m>(S_5:K)=|S_5|/|K|=120/5=24</m>.</li>
<li>In disjoint cycle notation, the permutation <m>(1245)(25)</m> is written <m>(12)(45)</m>, so <m>L</m> has order 2. Thus, <m>(S_6:L)=|S_6|/|L|=720/2=360</m>.</li>
</ol>
</p>
</solution>
</exercise>


<exercise>
<statement><p>Let <m>H</m> be the subgroup of <m>D_4</m> generated by <m>fr^2</m>.
<ol>
<li> Find the index of <m>H</m> in <m>D_4</m>.</li>
<li> Find the left and right cosets of <m>H</m> in
        <m>D_4</m>. Is <m>H\unlhd G</m>? </li>
  </ol></p>
</statement>

<solution>
<p>
<ol>
<li><m>(D_4:H)=|D_4|/|H|=8/2=4</m>.</li>
<li><m>H=\{e, fr^2\}</m>.  The left cosets of <m>H</m>
    in <m>D_4</m> are <m>H, rH=\{r, fr\}, r^2H=\{r^2,f\},</m>
    and <m>r^3H=\{r^3, fr^3\}</m>, and the right cosets
    of <m>H</m> in <m>D_4</m> are <m>H, Hr=\{r, fr^3\},
    Hr^2=\{r^2,f\},</m> and <m>Hr^3=\{r^3, fr\}</m>.  The
    left and right cosets of <m>H</m> in <m>D_4</m> are
    not the same, so <m>H</m> is not normal in <m>G</m>.</li>
    </ol>
    </p>
    </solution>

</exercise>

